As an Administrator, I need to retrieve all currently active override records, so that the UI can display all active overrides.  Acceptance Criteria
AC1: Retrieve Active Overrides with Details
Given multiple active override records exist in XBSS_LIFE_DIS_BAND_OVERRIDE When findAllActive() is called Then:
	•	Only records where the current date falls between startDate and endDate are returned
	•	Each record should include:
	◦	approverName
	◦	createdByName
	◦	lastUpdatedByName
	◦	companyName
	◦	exchange

AC2:
Given 3 active override records exist, each with different approverId and companyCode When findAllActive() is called Then:
	•	psDao.getEmployeesFullName(employeeIds) is called exactly once with all employee IDs batched
	•	psCompanyDao.findCompaniesNames(companyCodes) is called exactly once with all company codes batched

AC3
Given no active override records exist When findAllActive() is called Then:
	•	An empty list is returned
	•	No exception is thrown

